 :actor/purpose "A NEWS MEDIUM, kotoba-wasm-native, run on the Murakumo fleet. Two faces over one Datom log: (1) MIRROR — datafies the world's real news media (outlets · 面/sections · headlines · bylines · links) into the kotoba Datom log as an append-only as-of trail, matching the SURFACE (面) of actual news media (一面/政治/経済/国際/社会/文化/科学/スポーツ); (2) MEDIUM — the connective wire BETWEEN etzhayyim actors: each first-party actor's own Datom as-of events project into the matching 面 as :article/kind :actor-event, and every article carries :news.mention edges to the actors/entities it concerns, so the article×mention×面 graph IS the actor-to-actor wire (danjo finds → kawaraban carries → kanae renders; a chokepoint story links watari + watatsuna + mitooshi in one 面). The charter-clean inverse of a 'news app': a public-square mirror that links out, NEVER advertises (Charter-Rider §2), NEVER engagement-optimizes (Charter §1.13), NEVER profiles a reader (G3), NEVER republishes full copyrighted text (G4, link-out only), NEVER adjudicates truth (G1 — ake/danjo boundary), and NEVER speaks AS an outlet or another actor (G9, ADR-2606042330). Sibling boundary: kataribe 語部 IS etzhayyim's own press (a primary voice); kawaraban MIRRORS the world's press and WIRES the actors together (a medium, not a source — G11). Per ADR-2606061900."
 :actor/non-goals {"description" "6 explicitly excluded scopes", "goals" {"N1" "NOT a fact-checker / truth adjudicator — no verdict, no rating (G1; ake/danjo own correction & discrepancy)", "N2" "NOT an ad-funded / engagement-optimized feed — no paid placement, no addictive ranking (G2)", "N3" "NOT a personalized feed — no reader profile, no behavioral recommendation, no surveillance (G3)", "N4" "NOT a content republisher — headline + link + fair-use excerpt only, never the full body (G4)", "N5" "NOT an impersonator — never posts AS an outlet or AS another actor (G9)", "N6" "NOT a primary source — kawaraban authors no original first-person claim; it mirrors and wires (G11; kataribe is the primary voice)"}}
